ciscoFcipMgmtExtMIB.name: ciscoFcipMgmtExtMIB

revisions.description: Added the following objects in cfmFcipLinkExtTable: - cfmFcipLinkExtTapeReadAccOper - cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanL2k - cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanL4k - cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanLOper2k - cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanLOper4k

Added the following objects in cfmFcipLinkExtTable: cfmFcipLinkExtPhyIfIndex, cfmFcipLinkExtWriteAccOper, and cfmFcipLinkExtTapeAccOper. Also added a new table cfmFcipLinkExtStatsTable with objects: cfmFcipLinkStatsRxIPCompRatio and cfmFcipLinkStatsTxIPCompRatio.

Added following objects in cfmFcipLinkExtTable. cfmFcipLinkExtIPSec Added cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup1. Added following object in cfmFcipEntityExtTable. cfmFcipEntityExtTcpLocalPort. cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxJitter. cfmFcipEntityExtTcpSACKEnable. Added cfmFcipEntityExtGroupSup1. Added cfmFcipExtCompliance4.
Added following objects in cfmFcipLinkExtTable. cfmFcipLinkExtTapeAccelerator, cfmFcipLinkExtFlowCtrlBurstSize. Added cfmFcipLinkMapTable.
Added following objects in cfmFcipEntityExtTable. cfmFcipEntityExtCWMEnable, cfmFcipEntityExtCWMBurstSize.
Removed cfmFcipLinkExtIPCompAlgorithm and renamed object cfmFcipLinkExtIPCompPerf to cfmFcipLinkExtIPComp Added compliance statement for cfmFcipLinkExtTimestampTolerance.
Added: cfmFcipLinkExtEthIfIndex, cfmFcipLinkExtWriteAccelerator, cfmFcipLinkExtIPCompAlgorithm,cfmFcipLinkExtIPCompPerf. Updated the Compliance statement.
Modified ranges and added DEFVAL clause to objects: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpSendBufSize,cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxBW, cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinAvailBW, cfmFcipEntityExtTcpRndTrpTimeEst.

Modified objects: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpKeepAliveTO. Replaced: cfmFcipLinkExtLocalEntityMode with cfmFcipLinkExtLocalBPortEnable. cfmFcipEntityExtTcpInitRTO with cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinRTO. Added: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpSendBufSize, cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxBW,cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinAvailBW, cfmFcipEntityExtTcpRndTrpTimeEst,cfmFcipLinkExtCntrlQOSField, cfmFcipLinkExtDataQOSField. Removed cfmFcipEntityExtWindowSize.
Added objects cfmFcipLinkExtSpecialFrameEnable, cfmFcipLinkExtBPortKAEnable. Modified the range values for some objects.
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoFcipMgmtExtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553 -NETS E-mail: cs-san@cisco.com
ciscoFcipMgmtExtMIB.description: A MIB module for extending the CISCO-FCIP-MGMT-MIB to add objects which provide additional information about FCIP interfaces not available in other MIBS.

cfmFcipEntityExtTable.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTable
cfmFcipEntityExtTable.description: A table contains objects which provide more information of FCIP entity which is not available in CISCO-FCIP-MGMT-MIB.

cfmFcipEntityExtEntry.name: cfmFcipEntityExtEntry
cfmFcipEntityExtEntry.description: A entry into the cfmFcipEntityExtTable. Each entry contains attributes associated with an FCIP entity.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpKeepAliveTO.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpKeepAliveTO
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpKeepAliveTO.description: The TCP Keep alive timeout for all links within this entity.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxReTx.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxReTx
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxReTx.description: The Maximum number of times that the same item of data will be retransmitted over a TCP connection. If delivery is not acknowledged after this number of retransmissions then the TCP connection is terminated.

cfmFcipEntityExtPMTUEnable.name: cfmFcipEntityExtPMTUEnable
cfmFcipEntityExtPMTUEnable.description: The path MTU discovery is enabled if the value of this object is true(1), else it is disabled, and has the value false(2).

cfmFcipEntityExtPMTUResetTO.name: cfmFcipEntityExtPMTUResetTO
cfmFcipEntityExtPMTUResetTO.description: The time interval for which the discovered pathMTU is valid, before MSS reverts back to the negotiated TCP value. This object is writeble only if cfmFcipEntityExtPMTUEnable is 'true'.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinRTO.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinRTO
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinRTO.description: The TCP minimum retransmit timeout for all the links on this entity.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpSendBufSize.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpSendBufSize
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpSendBufSize.description: The aggregate TCP send window for all TCP connections on all Links within this entity. This value is used for Egress Flow Control. When the aggregate of the data queued on all connections within this entity reaches this value, the sender is flow controlled.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxBW.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxBW
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxBW.description: This is an estimate of the Bandwidth of the network pipe used for the B-D product computation, which lets us derive the TCP receive window to advertise. The cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxBW,cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinAvailBW, cfmFcipEntityExtTcpRndTrpTimeEst must be set in the same SNMP set request. SET operation would fail if this object is set individually.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinAvailBW.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinAvailBW
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinAvailBW.description: The minimum available bandwidth for the TCP connections on the Links within this entity. The cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxBW,cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinAvailBW, cfmFcipEntityExtTcpRndTrpTimeEst must be set in the same SNMP set request. SET operation would fail if this object is set individually.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpRndTrpTimeEst.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpRndTrpTimeEst
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpRndTrpTimeEst.description: This is an estimate of the round trip delay of the network pipe used for the B-D product computation, which lets us derive the TCP receive window to advertise. The cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxBW,cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMinAvailBW, cfmFcipEntityExtTcpRndTrpTimeEst must be set in the same SNMP set request. SET operation would fail if this object is set individually.

cfmFcipEntityExtCWMEnable.name: cfmFcipEntityExtCWMEnable
cfmFcipEntityExtCWMEnable.reference: Congestion Window Monitoring (Hughes, Touch, and Heidemann)
cfmFcipEntityExtCWMEnable.description: This object is used for enabling/disabling the congestion window monitoring. If the value of this object is true(1), it is enabled. It is disabled if the value is false(2).

cfmFcipEntityExtCWMBurstSize.name: cfmFcipEntityExtCWMBurstSize
cfmFcipEntityExtCWMBurstSize.description: The maximum burst sent after a tcp sender idle period. This object is writeble only if cfmFcipEntityExtCWMEnable is 'true'.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpSACKEnable.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpSACKEnable
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpSACKEnable.description: Setting the value to 'True', enables the Selective Acknowledgement (SACK) on this link.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpLocalPort.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpLocalPort
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpLocalPort.description: The local TCP port to which the local FCIP entity will connect if and when it initiates a TCP connection setup for this link.

cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxJitter.name: cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxJitter
cfmFcipEntityExtTcpMaxJitter.description: The maximum delay variation that is not due to congestion that can be experienced by TCP connections for all links on this entity.

cfmFcipLinkExtTable.name: cfmFcipLinkExtTable
cfmFcipLinkExtTable.description: A table contains objects which provide more information of FCIP link which is not available in CISCO-FCIP-MGMT-MIB.

cfmFcipLinkExtEntry.name: cfmFcipLinkExtEntry
cfmFcipLinkExtEntry.description: A entry into cfmFcipLinkExtTable. Each entry contains attributes associated with an FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkExtPassiveMode.name: cfmFcipLinkExtPassiveMode
cfmFcipLinkExtPassiveMode.description: If the value is set to 'false' this link endpoint actively tries to connect to the peer. If it is set to 'true' the link endpoint waits for the peer to connect to it.

cfmFcipLinkExtNumTcpConn.name: cfmFcipLinkExtNumTcpConn
cfmFcipLinkExtNumTcpConn.description: The maximum number of TCP connections allowed on this link.

cfmFcipLinkExtCheckTimestamp.name: cfmFcipLinkExtCheckTimestamp
cfmFcipLinkExtCheckTimestamp.description: The value is 'true', if the timestamp in FCIP header is to checked. If 'false' the timestamp is ignored.

cfmFcipLinkExtTimestampTolerance.name: cfmFcipLinkExtTimestampTolerance
cfmFcipLinkExtTimestampTolerance.reference: Section 29.2.1.2 E_D_TOV in FC-PH (Fibre Channel - Physical and Signaling Interface) Rev 4.3.
cfmFcipLinkExtTimestampTolerance.description: The accepted time difference between the local time and the timestamp value received in the FCIP header. By default this value will be EDTOV/2. EDTOV is the Error_Detect_Timeout Value used for Fibre channel Ports as the timeout value for detecting an error condition.

cfmFcipLinkExtTcpRemPort.name: cfmFcipLinkExtTcpRemPort
cfmFcipLinkExtTcpRemPort.description: The remote TCP port to which the local FCIP entity will connect if and when it initiates a TCP connection setup for this link.

cfmFcipLinkExtLocalBPortEnable.name: cfmFcipLinkExtLocalBPortEnable
cfmFcipLinkExtLocalBPortEnable.description: If the value is set to 'true', the B port mode is enabled on the local FCIP link. If set to 'false' the B port mode is disabled.

cfmFcipLinkExtSpecialFrameEnable.name: cfmFcipLinkExtSpecialFrameEnable
cfmFcipLinkExtSpecialFrameEnable.description: If the value is set to 'true', the TCP active opener initiates FCIP special frames and the TCP passive opener responds to the FCIP special frames. If it is set to 'false', the FCIP special frames are neither generated nor responded to.

cfmFcipLinkExtBPortKAEnable.name: cfmFcipLinkExtBPortKAEnable
cfmFcipLinkExtBPortKAEnable.reference: Section 15.5.4 Echo in FC-FS (Fibre Channel - Framing and Signaling ) Rev 0.50.
cfmFcipLinkExtBPortKAEnable.description: If the value is set to 'true', a message is sent in response to a (Fibre Channel) ELS Echo frame received from the peer. Some B Port implementations use ELS Echo request/response frames as Link Keep Alive. If it is set to 'false', this response is not generated. This object is valid only if the cfmFcipLinkExtLocalBPortEnable is 'true'.

cfmFcipLinkExtCntrlQOSField.name: cfmFcipLinkExtCntrlQOSField
cfmFcipLinkExtCntrlQOSField.description: The value to be set for the TOS field in IP header for the TCP control connection. The cfmFcipLinkExtCntrlQOSField,cfmFcipLinkExtDataQOSField must be set in the same SNMP set request. SET operation would fail if this object is set individually.

cfmFcipLinkExtDataQOSField.name: cfmFcipLinkExtDataQOSField
cfmFcipLinkExtDataQOSField.description: The value to be set for the TOS field in IP header for the TCP Data connection. The cfmFcipLinkExtCntrlQOSField,cfmFcipLinkExtDataQOSField must be set in the same SNMP set request. SET operation would fail if this object is set individually.

cfmFcipLinkExtEthIfIndex.name: cfmFcipLinkExtEthIfIndex
cfmFcipLinkExtEthIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface on which this FCIP link was initiated.

cfmFcipLinkExtWriteAccelerator.name: cfmFcipLinkExtWriteAccelerator
cfmFcipLinkExtWriteAccelerator.description: The Write accelerator allows for enhancing SCSI write performance. If 'true', the FCIP Write accelerator is enabled on this link If 'false' it is disabled.

cfmFcipLinkExtIPComp.name: cfmFcipLinkExtIPComp
cfmFcipLinkExtIPComp.description: The configuration for the IP compression. 'none' - ip compression is disabled. 'highCompressionRatio' - indicates better compression performance at the cost of lower throughput. 'highThroughput' - indicates better throughput at the cost of lower compression performance. 'auto' - indicates that an appropriate mode wll be picked based on the bandwidth and data. 'mode1' - fast compression mode for high bandwidth WAN links with bandwidth greater than 30 Mbps. 'mode2' - high compression mode for moderately low bandwidth WAN links, i.e. bandwidth between 15 and 30 Mbps. 'mode3' - high compression mode for low bandwidth WAN links, i.e. banwidth less than 15 Mbps.

cfmFcipLinkExtTapeAccelerator.name: cfmFcipLinkExtTapeAccelerator
cfmFcipLinkExtTapeAccelerator.description: The Tape accelerator allows for enhancing Tape write performance. If 'true', the FCIP Tape accelerator is enabled on this link If 'false' it is disabled.

cfmFcipLinkExtIPSec.name: cfmFcipLinkExtIPSec
cfmFcipLinkExtIPSec.description: Indicates whether the IP Security has been turned on or off on this link.

cfmFcipLinkExtPhyIfIndex.name: cfmFcipLinkExtPhyIfIndex
cfmFcipLinkExtPhyIfIndex.description: The physical ifIndex of the interface on which this FCIP link is currently bound.

cfmFcipLinkExtWriteAccOper.name: cfmFcipLinkExtWriteAccOper
cfmFcipLinkExtWriteAccOper.description: When Write Acceleration is operationally off for the FCIP link, the value of this object will be set to 'false'. When Write Acceleration is operationally on for the FCIP link, the value of this object will be set to 'true'.

cfmFcipLinkExtTapeAccOper.name: cfmFcipLinkExtTapeAccOper
cfmFcipLinkExtTapeAccOper.description: When Tape Acceleration is operationally off for the FCIP link, the value of this object will be set to 'false'. When Tape Acceleration is operationally on for the FCIP link, the value of this object will be set to 'true'.

cfmFcipLinkExtTapeReadAccOper.name: cfmFcipLinkExtTapeReadAccOper
cfmFcipLinkExtTapeReadAccOper.description: This object represents the state of the Tape Read Acceleration for an FCIP link. Tape Read Acceleration is automatically operational when Tape Acceleration is operational (cfmFcipLinkExtTapeAccOper) and both sides of the FCIP link support Tape Read Acceleration. When Tape Read Acceleration is operationally off for the FCIP link, the value of this object is 'false'. When Tape Read Acceleration is operationally on for the FCIP link, the value of this object is 'true'.

cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanL2k.name: cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanL2k
cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanL2k.description: The list of VSANs (in the range 1 through 2047) for which Ficon Tape Acceleration is configured. Only VSANs with a cficonVsanEntry of CISCO-FICON-MIB present can be configured for Ficon Tape Acceleration.

cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanL4k.name: cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanL4k
cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanL4k.description: The list of VSANs (in the range 2048 through 4096) for which Ficon Tape Acceleration is configured. Only VSANs with a cficonVsanEntry of CISCO-FICON-MIB present can be configured for Ficon Tape Acceleration.

cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanLOper2k.name: cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanLOper2k
cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanLOper2k.description: The list of VSANs (in the range 1 through 2047) for which Ficon Tape Acceleration is operationally ON.

cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanLOper4k.name: cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanLOper4k
cfmFcipLinkExtFiconTAVsanLOper4k.description: The list of VSANs (in the range 2048 through 4096) for which Ficon Tape Acceleration is operationally ON.

cfmFcipLinkMapTable.name: cfmFcipLinkMapTable
cfmFcipLinkMapTable.description: A table containing FCIP link index to Entity Identifier mapping for a FCIP link.

cfmFcipLinkMapEntry.name: cfmFcipLinkMapEntry
cfmFcipLinkMapEntry.description: A conceptual row of the FCIP link map table mapping the fcip link index to FCIP Entity Identifier.

cfmFcipLinkMapIndex.name: cfmFcipLinkMapIndex
cfmFcipLinkMapIndex.description: An arbitrary integer which uniquely identifies one FCIP link within a FCIP entity.

cfmFcipMapEntityId.name: cfmFcipMapEntityId
cfmFcipMapEntityId.description: The FCIP entity Identifier corresponding to the instance of cfmFcipLinkMapIndex.

cfmFcipLinkExtStatsTable.name: cfmFcipLinkExtStatsTable
cfmFcipLinkExtStatsTable.description: A table containing objects which provide status information of the FCIP link for the cfmFcipLinkExtTable configured information.

cfmFcipLinkExtStatsEntry.name: cfmFcipLinkExtStatsEntry
cfmFcipLinkExtStatsEntry.description: An entry into cfmFcipLinkExtStatsTable. Each entry contains attributes associated with an FCIP Link.

cfmFcipLinkStatsRxIPCompRatio.name: cfmFcipLinkStatsRxIPCompRatio
cfmFcipLinkStatsRxIPCompRatio.description: The IP Copmression ratio for received packets on the FCIP device. The value of this object will be presented as a floating point number with two digits after the decimal point.

cfmFcipLinkStatsTxIPCompRatio.name: cfmFcipLinkStatsTxIPCompRatio
cfmFcipLinkStatsTxIPCompRatio.description: The IP Copmression ratio for transmitted packets on the FCIP device. The value of this object will be presented as a floating point number with two digits after the decimal point.

cfmFcipExtCompliance.name: cfmFcipExtCompliance
cfmFcipExtCompliance.description: Compliance statement for FCIP Extension MIB.

cfmFcipExtCompliance1.name: cfmFcipExtCompliance1
cfmFcipExtCompliance1.description: Compliance statement for FCIP Extension MIB.

cfmFcipExtCompliance2.name: cfmFcipExtCompliance2
cfmFcipExtCompliance2.description: Compliance statement for FCIP Extension MIB.

cfmFcipExtCompliance3.name: cfmFcipExtCompliance3
cfmFcipExtCompliance3.description: Compliance statement for FCIP Extension MIB.

cfmFcipExtCompliance4.name: cfmFcipExtCompliance4
cfmFcipExtCompliance4.description: Compliance statement for FCIP Extension MIB.

cfmFcipExtCompliance5.name: cfmFcipExtCompliance5
cfmFcipExtCompliance5.description: Compliance statement for FCIP Extension MIB.

cfmFcipExtCompliance6.name: cfmFcipExtCompliance6
cfmFcipExtCompliance6.description: Compliance statement for FCIP Extension MIB.

cfmFcipEntityExtGroup.name: cfmFcipEntityExtGroup
cfmFcipEntityExtGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Entity.

cfmFcipLinkExtGroup.name: cfmFcipLinkExtGroup
cfmFcipLinkExtGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Links.

cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev1.name: cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev1
cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev1.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Links.

cfmFcipEntityExtCWMGroup.name: cfmFcipEntityExtCWMGroup
cfmFcipEntityExtCWMGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information on Congestion Window Monitoring of a FCIP Entity.

cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2.name: cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2
cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Links, especially about the tape acceleration.

cfmFcipLinkExtMapGroup.name: cfmFcipLinkExtMapGroup
cfmFcipLinkExtMapGroup.description: A collection of objects providing mapping between FCIP Links and their enrity Identifiers

cfmFcipEntityExtGroupSup1.name: cfmFcipEntityExtGroupSup1
cfmFcipEntityExtGroupSup1.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Entity.

cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup1.name: cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup1
cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup1.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Links, especially about the tape acceleration and IP Security.

cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup2.name: cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup2
cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup2.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Link Operational state.

cfmFcipLinkExtStatsGroup.name: cfmFcipLinkExtStatsGroup
cfmFcipLinkExtStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP statistics.

cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup3.name: cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup3
cfmFcipLinkExtGroupRev2Sup3.description: A collection of objects providing information about FCIP Link Tape Read and Ficon Tape Acceleration Configuration and Operational status.
